<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
	<!--
	  KisMac3 hardened-runtime entitlements (Developer ID, S8.x / Milestone 14).

	  This app is NOT sandboxed. Do NOT add com.apple.security.app-sandbox here:
	  KisMac needs raw libpcap/BPF, IOKit, CoreWLAN, CoreBluetooth and the
	  Apple80211 private framework, none of which work under the App Sandbox.
	  These keys configure the *hardened runtime* only (ENABLE_HARDENED_RUNTIME),
	  which is the Notarization requirement, and are deliberately minimal.

	  Each entry below is present because the app genuinely needs it; anything
	  not listed is intentionally denied. See docs/release.md for the rationale
	  and the known pcap/BPF-under-hardened-runtime limitation.
	-->

	<!--
	  Bundled frameworks (BIGL.framework, BIGeneric.framework) and the GBStorage
	  code are signed with the SAME Developer ID team (DMP42GVPJ3) by
	  scripts/sign_export.sh, so library validation is LEFT ENABLED (the key
	  below is commented out on purpose). Only uncomment
	  com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation if you must load a
	  framework signed by a DIFFERENT team identity, and document why in
	  docs/release.md. Prefer re-signing everything with one team instead.

	<key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
	<true/>
	-->

	<!--
	  Intentionally EMPTY. The com.apple.security.personal-information.location,
	  com.apple.security.device.bluetooth and com.apple.security.device.usb keys
	  are APP-SANDBOX entitlements; on this non-sandboxed app they are inert and
	  were removed (final review C3).

	  Location, Bluetooth and Local Network access are handled at runtime via TCC
	  (the system permission prompts), driven by the NS*UsageDescription strings
	  in Info.plist (NSLocationWhenInUseUsageDescription,
	  NSBluetoothAlwaysUsageDescription, NSLocalNetworkUsageDescription), NOT by
	  hardened-runtime entitlements. Raw USB/IOKit access also needs no
	  entitlement on a non-sandboxed app.

	  An empty entitlements <dict/> is the correct, complete configuration for a
	  hardened-runtime, non-sandboxed Developer ID build (hardened runtime stays
	  enabled via the ENABLE_HARDENED_RUNTIME Release build setting).
	-->
</dict>
</plist>
